{{ about|the Township of Hayesville|the Town of the same name|Hayesville, North Carolina}}

[[Image:Map of Clay County North Carolina With Municipal and Township Labels.PNG|thumb|300px|Map of Clay County, North Carolina With Municipal and Township Labels]]

'''Hayesville''' is a central [[Township]], and one of the six townships of [[Clay County, North Carolina|Clay County]], [[North Carolina]], [[United States]]. The other five are [[Brasstown,_North_Carolina|Brasstown]], Hiawassee, Shooting Creek, Sweetwater, and Tusquittee.

===Cities and Towns===
Hayesville is home to the county seat, [[Hayesville,_North_Carolina|Hayesville]] a the town of the same name.

